text: It is hard to find a stall that makes such nostalgic pancakes after the closing of the Lavender hawker centre. Get your quick fix here.
Delicious thin and crispy pancakes for a reasonable price! Many flavours available and I was able to customise a chocolate + cheese flavor. Will definitely drop by more!

Good snacks for young and old. Our favorite is chocolate, ham and cheese. Be prepared to wait if it is very crowded. You can order early but it is nice while hot. If it is cold, you can bake it reheat. Pricing is standard for HDB area. Best time to go is off peak during 3-5pm, timing for your tea break snacks.

Traditional Ming Jiang Kuey with a modern twist to suit our new style of having in many choices to chose from. They are also serving the traditional simplicity of coconut | peanut | red bean. With improvised equipment and smaller size makes this local delight not a usual breakfast item but a quick snack with reasonable pricing anytime of the day. üëçüèªü§©
Price has gone up since the covid-19.. standard still good and lady selling the pancake is friendly to remind me that pancake cost $1.3 each.. haha.
